name: Central big room - ap with balcony
description:
A bargain in Oslo!!
Room in new and fully furnitured apartement with waching mashine, dishwasher, microwave, dishes, bedding, dunes, towels, internet access, a small balcony and so on... all you need for a nice time in the capitol of Norway.
neighborhood_overview:
The apartment is situated in the eastern part of Oslo. Vålerenga is a charming part of Oslo with small restaurants and local bars, idyllic wooden buildings and beautiful Vålerenga park where the locals like to gather for picnics and sun bathing. The neighborhood is nice, urban and diverse. It is a quiet but central area of Oslo. This area is populated by a lovely mix of students, couples and families - young and old from all over the world.
Right outside the apartment there are various grocery stores, even one which is open on Sundays. If you dont want to do the cooking I have an excellent sushi place across the road. I also have a pizza place, a spanish tapas place and three pubs around the corner. If you walk 10 minutes from my area you will find a never-ending story of various shops, restaurants and bars as you get closer to downtown.
host_about: I am a social 59 year old woman. Take a look at my guests reviews to learn more about me :-)

description: Situated in a safe, quiet and central area of Oslo in a cosy neighbourhood by the picturesque Akerselva-river. My condA short walk from the lively Grünerløkka-area, and close by public transport.
neighborhood_overview:
Groceries:
There is a small Joker convenience store around the corner, for basic odd hours shopping.
Super-markets:
Meny Ringnes Park, Sannergata 6C ( 400 m)
Coop Mega Alexander Kiellands Plass, Waldemar Thranes gate 72 (350 m)
REMA 1000 Darres Gate , Darres gate 2 (300m).

Cinema: Ringen Kino ( 700 meters)

Playground. There is a huge playground in the Iladalen Park for kids. There is also a small area to play in the backyard.

Running/ Biking. Run up and down along the river. You can follow the river all the way up to the Nordmarka forest and Maridalsvannet (5-6 km) and from there you can run as long as you like in the first.

An early Airbnb adopter in Norway - living in Oslo and Berlin.

Non-smoker, reliable in payments, and always mindful of others' spaces. I genuinely enjoy meeting new people through Airbnb, either as a host or a guest. 

Can't wait for the next adventure.

description:
House located only 3km from Oslo city center & 10min walk to the Frognerpark also known as the Vigerlandspark! Perfect for 2 couples or 1 family of maximum 3 children. Close to Skøyen traffic hub (trains, busses, tram and metro line).

3 toalettes, two showers, 1 bathtub, dining table outside on large terrace and large dining table inside. Two bedrooms for kids, 1 master bedroom. A «kjellerstue»/guestroom/home cinema. An office and wifi makes it easy to work from home.
neighborhood_overview: Karenslyst allee is our nearest "high street" with bakery, hairdresser, shops and restaurants. The Vigerlands Park is another favourite - for running or taking photos of the sculptures. There is also a massive playground for children here. Nearest cinema and bars are around Majorstua area.

host_about:
I am an adventurous and active girl, recently graduated from UC Berkeley and I am currently working for Tesla Motors. I am originally from Norway and that is where is where I currently live, but I love to travel and I have spent a large part of my upbringing abroad. I grew up in both New Zealand and Dubai, and just moved home from Berkeley, California where I studied for five years. 

I am very active, flexible, easy going and fun-loving. I love adventures and exploring new places, as well as getting to know new people along the way! When I travel, I usually stay away from tourist sites, as I love to just explore on my own and get to know the backbone and hidden secrets of cities and new places.

I used to be a professional rower and train for the Norwegian national team, so I like to stay in activity. If I visit a place that has good hiking or running areas, I always try them out.

Finally, I am also a huge foodlover and I spend a lot of my time exploring the foods of the places I go to.

name: Spacious and charming house in central  Oslo
description: We have a nice and fresh house with 5  bedrooms, two bathrooms, and a big garden central in Oslo. It has a big terrace, a cosy chill out corner, and a trampoline. Close to all public transport, 15 min away from the city center. The house is close to recreational areas, shopping centers, Odeon Cinema, Grunerløkka, the Vigeland Park,  and the Oslofjord etc. The airport bus stops four minutes walk from the house. Ideal for families, or larger groups. Nice, quiet and safe area of Oslo.
neighborhood_overview:
Our neighborhood is quiet and very safe, and at the same time also central. It has one of Norway's biggest shopping malls close by, and only a short travel away from the cosy shops and cafes of Grünerløkka. It's child friendly and easy access to hiking facilities, it's basically the best place in Oslo to live! The subway and tram will take you anywhere you need to go. The airport bus stops 5 minutes away from the house.

Grefsenkollen is a beautiful place where you can enjoy great food and the breathtaking view of Oslo! Close by is also Trollvann (Troll lake) which is a great place for bathing in fresh water, and for hiking or biking in the forrest.

At Storo (5 min away) you'll find the brand new cinema Odeon which has the biggestt IMAX screen in Scandinavia!
host_about: I'm an actor and director from Norway and I live in Oslo with my husband, who's also an actor, and our three kids. We hope to house people from all over the world and we're looking forward to having nice people staying with us.

name: Klassisk Oslo-leilighet
neighborhood_overview:
Cozy and safe neighborhood with proximity to the city center. Old Oslo has classic architecture, many cozy parks (Botanical Garden, Klosterenga Sculpture Park, Medieval Park) and good Cafes. Recommend a ride to Handbaked! Or up to the cosy wooden house building at Kampen to visit Farine cafe.
Nearest subway station is Tøyen (8 min walk from the apartment) Here all the subway lines go, and there are only 2 stops to Oslo S. In Tøyen Square you will find everything you would need; restaurants, bars, cafes, pharmacy, flower shop and library.
The Oslo Bay with the Munch Museum and the Opera is a short walk away and can offer fantastic restaurants, great shopping and a pleasant harbor promenade.

name: Charming, central, and big garden
description:
This family wooden house is located in a very charming neighborhood in central Oslo. The house is spacious and has a beautiful garden. Perfect for families or a group of friends.

Minimum of 3 nights. Shorter stay get in touch.
neighborhood_overview: Grocery shopping can be done at Rema 1000, KIWI and at Lille Tøyen kolonial, which also has a cafe and serves lunch. For further service offerings, Ensjø and Hasle Torg have a good selection. Only a short walk away is also Tøyen centre, Carl Berner shopping center and Fyrstikktorget. In addition, it is within walking distance of all Oslo's shopping streets with all the capital's facilities and service offerings. By car from Lille Tøyen, it takes approx. 3 minutes to Carl Berner, 5 minutes to Oslo S, 7 minutes to Majorstua and 30 minutes to Oslo Airport. Grünerløkka with its vibrant nightlife and numerous restaurants is only approx. 15 minutes away on foot.
host_about:
It is a real pleasure to be able to offer you a place to stay while in Oslo. I really love Oslo and what it has to offer. I have been living in Oslo since 1999 and originally I'm from the deep fjords on the west coast of Norway. I live in Oslo with my three children and husband. In my spare time I like to explore nature in and in the surrounding areas of Oslo, and also I love the different food cultures that are available in the city. I like to discover new places and meet new people. 

I'm the co-funder of cCHANGE Transformation in a Changing Climate (www.cchange.no), a platform for generating personal, cultural, and systems transformations in a changing climate. 

Look forward to hear from you!

name: Walking distance to the best of Oslo (and 2 baths)
description: Our 3-bedroom appartment sits at the edge of the forest overlooking the Opera, Holmenkollen and Barcode. Short walking distance downtown Oslo and Central Station, Ekeberg football fields (Norway Cup) and if you prefer -  a swim in the Oslofjord.
neighborhood_overview:
The apartment is located in Gamlebyen, an attractive area mixing the oldest part of Oslo with new and expressive arcitecture in Barcode - famed in international magazines, saunas and beaches at Sørenga, the Opera, newly opened Munch museum and Deichman public library (advise a visit), lots of restaurants and interesting shops with Norwegian design.

The apartment overlooks the middle age park (Middelalderparken) the oldest part of Oslo where you will find remnants of the old city and archeological sites, up the hill there are rune-painted stones. A 15 min. walk uphill through the sculpture park, you will reach Ekeberg football fields where Norway Cup each summer attract football teams from all over the world.
There is also an open public farm with animals and horseback riding, minigolf and playgrounds, kiting, cricket, great hiking/running trail, fine dining at Ekeberg Restaurant surrounded by the beautiful sculpture park.

Nearby trams (13+19) take you do

name: Beautiful studio apt. in the heart of Oslo!
description: Welcome to a perfect place for couples, solo adventurers, and business travelers! This charming studio will make you feel like home due to its cozyness and the best location in Oslo. It's modern, light, convenient, situated on a quiet side street, yet just a few minutes away from a lively city centre. In this part of Oslo, named Frogner you will find art galleries, antique stores, places to eat or drink, whether you are looking for a nice gourmet restaurant or a cosy neighbourhood café.
neighborhood_overview:
Frogner is a borough and an exclusive residential and retail district in the West End of the city. In addition to traditional Frogner, the borough incorporates Bygdøy, Uranienborg and Majorstuen.
This is a very beautiful neighbourhood with 18th centuries buildings, parks, restaurants, shops, churches, art galleries, clubs, essential kiosks.
host_about:
Hello travellers! 
I am happy to live in times when people are more mobile than ever, traveling is easy and communities emerge thanks to such amazing services as Airbnb! 
I like the concept introduced by Taiye Selasi about being "multi-local" referring to people "who feel at home in the town where they grew up, the city they live now and maybe another place or two" - this describes me very well. I was born and raised in a multi-ethnic Kyrgyz Republic, graduated from a high school in the US, and now live and work in Oslo for almost 12 years. 

My professional background is in Radio & TV. Currently I work in a tech company providing online marketing services. Good conversations, long walks, dancing and being in the mountains are some of my energy sources. 

I love people and I love travelling, so Airbnb is my kind of service! I traveled and used Airbnb in Portugal, Spain, the US, Poland, Belize, Mexico, Belgium and absolutely loved it! Now, that I have an opportunity to host myself, I am excited to use all the knowledge and experience to make it a pleasant stay for my own guests.  

I look forward to meeting you, be it at your or my place!

name: Best location!
description:
Velkommen til Grünerløkka
Som Vouge skriver:

No neighborhood better embodies Oslo’s coming-of-age than Grünerløkka, with an attitude and energy that is reminiscent of New York’s Williamsburg or Bushwick, Montreal’s Mile End, and Los Angeles’s Silver Lake. As with so many equivalent neighborhoods around the world, it was once a haven for artists and creatives, but today is the heart of the city’s food, coffee, mixology, and shopping scenes. This is where you want to be next time you’re in Norway

description: Modern 3-bedroom apartment in very central location.
neighborhood_overview:
The apartment is centrally located in the heart of Oslo. Walking distance to Karl johans street in under 10, and only 5 minutes to the food hall Vulkan. The Munch museum and the Opera are about 15 minutes of walking distance past Karl Johan. Slottsparken and Vigelandsparken are fantastic to visit if you want to see Norwegian arts and culture. Perfect for family activity.

There are many lovely cafes nearby especially one located in the bend called cigarette & coffee, or Tranen that are also close by. Short distance to shopping which is best either at Karl Johan street or Bogstadveien. Favorite restaurant is the Monastery which is 3 minutes walk distance, and wine & food house in Markveien. Both have traditional Norwegian cuisine with exclusivity.

Please do not hesitate to ask for more recommendations.

neighborhood_overview:
One of the most popular districts in Oslo, Grünerløkka is constantly evolving. In Sannergata you are about 8 minutes walk from central Olaf Ryes Plass and Ringnes Park with Ringen Kino, Elixia, grocery and pharmacy is only a few minutes walk from the apartment.

At Løkka you will find several cozy park areas, popular restaurants, cafes, and bars.

Olaf Rye's place is known for its market days with its bustling folk life and events. Then you will find, among other things, a sea of food stalls and offers from Grünerløkkas local shops. Here it can also be mentioned that Birkelunden arranges secondhand market every Sunday. The onion life is synonymous with lazy days in the grass in the many great parks.

Birkelunden and Sofienbergparken are a favorite place with a good book or with good friends.

Feel free to also take the trip across the Akerselva to Vulkan, where former industrial areas have transformed into an exciting mecca for food, creativi
host_about:

I am a professional man living at Grunerløkka. I am friendly, outgoing and like to meet new people. 

It's important for me to provide a safe and comfortable rental in the heart of the city.

name: Beautiful 3-bedroom apartment,best of Grünerløkka!
description:
Hello,
we are renting out our bright and cozy 90 sqm apartment in central Oslo/ Grünerløkka. It´s located overviewing Sofienbergpark and you will find everything you need around the corner. The real Oslo street life with its cafés, bars and restaurants.

The apartment has an open Kitchen- and living space with high ceilings and a view on the park (gorgeous trees, a playground and green space to socialize).

The apartment has 3 bedrooms, a south facing balcony and a large, bright bathroom.
!
neighborhood_overview:
Grünerløkka is one of Oslo’s hippest areas, known for its street art, stylish bars, happening dance clubs and mellow cafes. Indie boutiques sell design items and vintage fashions, while weekend markets on neighborhood squares draw crowds for artisan eats, kitchenware, jewelry and bric-a-brac. Walking trails follow the Akerselva River, which is also flanked by small quirky parks and cool industrial concert venues.
The apartment is walking distance to the city centre and many of the major sights of Oslo.
host_about:
Hi!
We both, like you enjoy visiting new places as much as we can. 
Therefore we know from our experience that the good memory of a place stays stronger with having a warm home to stay.
Our goal is to provide comfortable and affordable accommodation with beautiful detail trying to provide what we look for in a place when we are on the road. 

Looking forward hearing from you!

description:

neighborhood_overview:
Formerly an old container dock, Sørenga in Oslo has been transformed into a brand new neigbourhood by the Oslo fjord. The area consists of residential complexes with exciting architectural details, and welcomes both residents and visitors to enjoy life at the water’s edge.

A green park with several channels stretches through the whole neighbourhood. At the southernmost tip you’ll find Sørenga Seawater Pool, a popular recreational spot for Oslovians in summertime. Several waterfront restaurants offer great food and two grocery stores in maritime surroundings, with a view to Oslo landmarks such as Barcode, the Oslo Opera House and Akershus Fortress. Sørenga is also a popular place for paddling.

Clean cozy apartment with one bedroom, one livingroom with an open kitchen, and a bathroom. The apartment is well equipped with washing machine, dishwasher, oven, kitchen accessories, flat screen tv, wifi...

Located in a quiet area with limeted traffic passing by the building.

Perfect for couples or people travelling alone!
neighborhood_overview:
Experience the vibrant life in Oslo's old working class area, Grünerløkka!

Cozy shopping streets, charming cafes and exciting eateries: Grünerløkka is a warm and vibrant neighborhood. Here you can find designs, flea markets and vintage treasures, have a barbecue in the park, or enjoy outdoor dining under the open sky and atmospheric lights.

In the quaint streets of the district, skateboards and strollers live in harmony, and Grünerløkka is perfect for exploring by foot. Akerselva river offers fantastic hiking opportunities through remnants of exciting industrial history, through greeneries, past Mathallen, Blå and DOGA.

Just north of Grünerløkka lies Torshov with a restaurant scene where something new is constantly happening, the Soria Moria stage house and the improvisational laboratory The Andre Teater - one of Oslo's unknown cultural gems.

If you are visting Oslo, this is definately the place to stay!
host_about:
30 years old, from Norway, currently working in Oslo.
I am easy going, social and openminded. I love to do sports and outdoor activities! Don't hesitate to contact me if you have any questions regarding my apartment or Oslo in general!

Cheers

neighborhood_overview:
In this charming neighborhood, you'll experience an unbeatable combination of exciting adventures and a cozy atmosphere. Wake up to the scent of freshly brewed coffee from the quaint cafes around the corner and take a stroll along the picturesque streets where you'll be greeted with smiles and friendly greetings from the neighbors.

There's something for everyone here! Explore the small shops with handmade treasures and unique souvenirs that you won't find anywhere else. Or why not embark on a culinary adventure and sample the local cuisine at the trendy restaurants and charming food stalls? For the adventurous souls, there are thrilling outdoor activities and parks to explore, perfect for a picnic or a bike ride in the sunshine.

The neighborhood's nightlife is also outstanding! Get caught up in the pulsating music at the trendy clubs and bars or settle down at one of the cozy pubs to enjoy live music and engaging conversations with the locals.

Not far from the house is the new Jordal Amphitheater and Jordal sports park. Adjacent to this you will find artificial turf, skating rink, skate park and a large playground. Close by is also Kampen church / Thorbjørn own place. It is also a short way to Tøyenbadet, as well as to the new Intility Arena, Valle Hovin and Valhall Arena. name: Scandinavian design by the fjord
description:
On the fjord, and canals, Vannkunsten, is an architectural highlight of Oslo.

If architecture is the king of this apartment, then location is certainly the queen. Sip coffee on the balcony while looking at the fjord. Use our stand up paddleboards to see the Snøhetta-made Opera House from a new perspective. Take the elevator down for a picnic by the waterfront and then try out the newly opened public beach next to the Opera House. We're steps away from Munch Museum, restaurants. Luxury fun!
neighborhood_overview:
This is Oslo's best urban neighborhood. The unique location of our building -- Vannkunsten -- provides a short walk to the best the city and nature has to offer. How about a morning bath at Oslo's new favorite bathing place, Sørenga sea bath? Or a cup of coffee on an outdoor terrace along Havnepromenaden, while you look out over the fjord?

The Oslofjord is led in between the buildings around us contributing to a maritime experience. At the same time, the pleasant neighborhood streets are filled with life and neighborhood atmosphere when new restaurants and shops open at street level.

By staying centrally in Bjørvika, short walks take you to the historic Medieval Park, and to the forest area and art trails in Ekebergparken. Here you get everything you could want in one place, in the heart of Oslo's new city center.

name: New apartment in Grünerløkka with terrace
description:
This new 45m2 apartment is located in the central neighborhood of Grûnerløkka.

The heart of Grûnerløkka is in 5-10 min walking distance from the apartment. The area is known as the urban neighborhood, with hip cafes and vintage shops. The unique and protective neighborhood of Rodeløkka is about 1 min away - a must to look at the small colorful wooden houses.

Carl Berners plass - Oslo's best hub - is about 2 min away. Here you will find everything by bus, tram and subway. It takes about 10 min by public transport to Oslo S
neighborhood_overview:
The neighborhood is called Rodeløkka and is part of the neighborhood Grûnerløkka. Rodeløkka is a unique area of Oslo, with about a hundred small wooden houses of various colors that date back to the 19th century. Large parts of the area are protected and I recommend guests to take a stroll in the cozy streets.

Rodeløkka Colonial Garden, Oslo's oldest, is also only a short walk from the apartment and is worth a visit.

Otherwise you will find everything Grûnerløkka has to offer - shops, cafés, bars and parks - in 5-10 min walk from the apartment.

name: Smart apartment with Balcony in Vibrant Oslo
description: Experience Oslo's vibrancy in our modern, 5th-floor apartment located in the emerging SoSoPa district. Our 50 sq m sanctuary offers a tranquil bedroom, open-plan living area with a pull-out bed, luxurious bathroom, and a balcony with afternoon sun. Boasting modern amenities and within walking distance to Grünerløkka's independent shops, parks, and cultural hotspots. Close to public transport for city-wide exploration.
neighborhood_overview:
Our apartment is situated in the heart of Oslo, nestled between the trendy Grünerløkka district and the emerging SoSoPa area. These vibrant neighborhoods encapsulate the city's dynamic culture, delightful cuisine, and charming local vibe.

Grünerløkka, often likened to Brooklyn, is a creative hub filled with independent boutiques, vintage shops, and artist studios, offering a unique shopping experience. It's also a culinary hotspot, boasting a range of restaurants, bars, and cafés. Among these is our favorite local café/bar, Gråbein, known for its inviting ambiance and tasty menu. Another favorite is Apostrophe, perfect for enjoying a glass of wine in the sun. The popular local restaurant, Little Pickle, is right on our block and offers a delightful dining experience. For beer enthusiasts, Schous, a local brewery, is just a 2-minute walk away and has a bar in the cellar.

name: Beautiful, central apartment in downtown Oslo <3
description:
♣ Classical apartment from the late 1800's in historical part of Oslo
♣ Very central location on a hidden away, quiet street
Spacious feeling with high ceiling, century old wooden floors and decor
Ruins of the Old City and a nice park right across the street
♣ Fully equipped flat with everything you need
♣ In walking distance of:
-Central station 10min
-Bjørvika/Opera 10min
-Sørenga and Grønland 5min (culture)
- Halfards Plass, Harald Hardrådes Plass, Medieval Park 2min (Commute)
neighborhood_overview:
Nice and friendly neighbourhood.

Very central apartment, but on an off-grid street with few passers by.
A nice park with several historical ruins right outside the door.
Nice restaurants close by are ZZ Pizza and Il Professore, a local, brown pub called Klosterenga often has live music.

Nearby neighbourhoods thrive in foods and nightlife:
Go for the pocket friendly and exotic area of Grønland to find food from all over the world - or go down to Sørenga where you have plenty og high class food. For drinks in this area check out Hammerhai, Mike's Corner or the skybar at Munch-museum
Try Arv kafe in Schweigaardsgate for a funky shop with a nice norwegian waffle with brown goats cheese! - Same street GOD - Gamle Oslo Delikatesse where you can get fine cheeses and meats

Several stores (Joker, Matkroken, Bunnpris, Unik) few minutes away
The apartment is close to the train line, but the train cannot be heard from the apartment

name: Nice room in classical apartment in  downtown Oslo
description:
♣ Classical apartment from the late 1800's in historical part of Oslo
♣ Very central location on a hidden away, quiet street
Spacious feeling with high ceiling, century old wooden floors and decor
Ruins of the Old City and a nice park right across the street
♣ Fully equipped flat with everything you need
♣ In walking distance of:
-Central station 12min
-Bjørvika/Opera 10min
-Sørenga and Grønland 5min (culture)
- Halfards Plass, Harald Hardrådes Plass, Medieval Park 2min (Commute)

Nice and friendly neighbourhood.

Very central apartment, but on an off-grid street with few passers by.
A nice park with several historical ruins right outside the door.
Nice restaurants close by are ZZ Pizza and Il Professore, a local, brown pub called Klosterenga often has live music.

Nearby neighbourhoods thrive in foods and nightlife:
Go for the pocket friendly and exotic area of Grønland to find food from all over the world - or go down to Sørenga where you have plenty og high class food. For drinks in this area check out Hammerhai, Mike's Corner or the skybar at Munch-museum
Try Arv kafe in Schweigaardsgate for a funky shop with a nice norwegian waffle with brown goats cheese! - Same street GOD - Gamle Oslo Delikatesse where you can get fine cheeses and meats

Several stores (Joker, Matkroken, Bunnpris, Unik) few minutes away
The apartment is close to the train line, but the train cannot be heard from the apartment

Everything you need within 5-10 minutes walk, including shopping center, cinema, restaurant, bakery, pharmacy, wine monopoly etc.

neighborhood_overview:
Quiet and quiet neighborhood, with great hiking and green spaces in the immediate vicinity. Voldsløkka sports park is a few minutes walk away, and is great for running/ jogging for a few rounds.

Bjølsen Park is also nearby, a quiet and nicely sheltered park with benches and large grass areas.

Along the Akerselva right outside the door, there are also lovely green spaces, and great for settling in with a book or throwing some stick with a dog coming by with their owner!

In Nydalen it is a popular little swimming area in the river and if you want to get a little sweaty first it's a nice walk up to Nydalsdammen, or a little further up- Freeze/ Brekkedammen for a refreshing swim!

There are cafes, bakeries, bars, restaurants and coffee shops both at Sagene, Bjølsen and in Nydalen.

On Bjølsen is the restaurant Mat and Mer with lovely food based on seasonal ingredients. The Halloumiburger at Tiffany's is a recommendation!

neighborhood_overview:
Frogner is a picturesque and vibrant area in the heart of Oslo that offers a unique blend of urban amenities and natural beauty. It is renowned for its lush green spaces, stunning architecture, and rich cultural heritage, making it a popular destination for both locals and tourists.

Visitors to Frogner can enjoy a stroll through the world-famous Frogner Park, which features over 200 bronze, granite, and cast iron sculptures by Gustav Vigeland, one of Norway's most celebrated artists. The park also has several playgrounds, picnic areas, and walking trails, making it an ideal spot for families and outdoor enthusiasts.

In addition to its natural attractions, Frogner boasts an array of charming cafes, trendy restaurants, and boutique shops that cater to a diverse range of tastes and interests. Visitors can sample authentic Norwegian cuisine, indulge in a variety of international delicacies, or simply soak up the local atmosphere in one of the area's many cafes or bars

Located in one of Oslo's most attractive and fashionable residential areas. The apartment has a high standard, private, undisturbed and sunny roof terrace and parking in closed garage facility. The building has an elevator.

Classic touches mixed with a stylish and modern design lend the quirkiness and Nordic elegance. Optimal floor plan and with tower room the apartment is completely unique.

neighborhood_overview:
The property has an attractive location in one of the city's most fashionable neighborhoods on Frogner. The apartment is located in a well-established area, consisting of pretty neat and classic city farms. The settlement on Frogner is characterized by large city villas and upscale rural farms from the 19th century, and today most embassies and embassy retreats are located there.

In this area you will find several great parks such as Hydroparken, Slottsparken and beautiful Frognerparken. The latter has the sculpture facility Vigelandsparken, Oslo City Museum, Frognerbadet and Frogner stadium. The home also has a short distance to delicious bathing areas on Bygdøy. Also on Bygdøy you will find museums such as the Norwegian Folk Museum, the Framed Museum, the Kon Tiki Museum, the Norwegian Maritime Museum and the Vikingsskipshuset. Gimle Kino and more attractive gyms etc. Short walk to The National Theatre, Vika, Aker Brygge, Tjuvholmen, Bogstadveien, Bygdøy Allé and Majorstue

name: Top floor, Grunerløkka district
description:
Peaceful accommodation with a central location in the district of Grunerløkka. The apartment is in the top floor, with 8 m2 balcony. From here you have a nice view of the neighborhood and the Oslo fjord.

The apartment is located in a quiet alley in an otherwise lively area right by Carl Berner with hubs for the bus, tram and the metro. The apartment faces out to a nice backyard with lawn. Nearby you will find several large parks (Torshovdalen, Botanical Garden at Tøyen), Vinmonopol, many grocery stores and nice bars.
neighborhood_overview:
The neighbourhood is nice and quiet, with a small park area just outside the apartment. If you want bigger spaces to wander about, Torshovdalen park is just around the corner. 2-3 buss stops away you will find Oslo Botaniske Hage (the botanical garden) and Tøyenparken. In the vicinity of Botanisk Hage and Tøyenparken you also find Tøyen Torg: A cozy downtown area for locals who likes to have drinks and food.

Even closer you find Carl Bernes Plass. Carl Berners Plass is a hub for the t-bane (metro), trams and busses that frequents the city center. From here, you can commute to almost anywhere in Oslo within minutes. Carl Berners Plass also has a myriad of bars, cafes, shops and stores.

Within walking distance you also find the center of the Grunerløkka-district with all it's bars, cafes and overall vibrant nightlife.
host_about: My name is Carl-Joachim, and I'm a norwegian situated in Oslo. I'm 37 years old and work as a teacher in chemistry and biology. I'm not making much noise as I prefer to read books and play chess:)

name: Unik leilighet i Grünerløkka
description:
Welcome to this unique and creative apartment in the heart of Grünerløkka, Oslo!

Grocery store just across the street and minutes to tram, subway and bus. Experience charming Rodeløkka as well as the lively diversity of Grünerløkka with restaurants and shops.

The modern 58 sqm apartment has an open living room/kitchen solution and a well-equipped kitchen. Enjoy entertainment on the TV with Sonos sound system or relax on the glorious balcony. Perfect for couples, friends, and solo travelers!
neighborhood_overview: The apartment is located in Rodeløkka, a charming historic neighborhood with a village atmosphere in the middle of the city. The neighborhood is located between Carl Berners Square and trendy Grünerløkka, with a selection of bars, restaurants and shops. The area is known for its old wooden houses that were basically built as a suburb of Christiania outside the city limits in the expansion of urban areas in 1859, and then there was a ban on building wooden houses in the city. This is therefore one of Oslo's few areas with this classic Norwegian village vibe. In 1988, the remaining wooden houses in the area were declared worthy of preservation.
host_about: Jeg ble født svært nysgjerrig og har alltid vært fasinert av mennesker, hvordan vi relaterer oss til hverandre og til denne svevende kulen vi liker å kalle "Jorda". Dette ledet meg til en grad i klimafysikk, etterfulgt av koordinator for den norske CERN-forskningen og nå Future leaders Global. På fritiden er jeg svært kreativ og elsker dans, fotografi, dikt og musikk. Og ja, jeg spiser desserten før middag.

neighborhood_overview:
Frogner is a vibrant and affluent neighborhood located in the heart of Oslo, Norway. Known for its charm and elegance, Frogner is a captivating blend of history, culture, and modernity.

At the center of Frogner lies the iconic Vigeland Park, a sprawling sculpture park created by renowned Norwegian sculptor Gustav Vigeland. The park is a masterpiece, showcasing over 200 sculptures that depict the human experience in various forms. The most famous of these sculptures is the monolithic "Monolith," a towering column of intertwined figures that stands as the park's centerpiece.

Frogner is also home to some of Oslo's most prestigious addresses, with leafy tree-lined streets, historic architecture, and luxurious homes. The neighborhood boasts a vibrant cultural scene, with numerous art galleries, theaters, and museums, including the Oslo City Museum and the Munch Museum, dedicated to the works of famous Norwegian artist Edvard Munch.

neighborhood_overview: The apartment is located in Rodeløkka, a charming historic neighborhood with a village atmosphere in the middle of the city. The neighborhood is located between Carl Berners Square and trendy Grünerløkka, with a selection of bars, restaurants and shops. The area is known for its old wooden houses that were basically built as a suburb of Christiania outside the city limits in the expansion of urban areas in 1859, and then there was a ban on building wooden houses in the city. This is therefore one of Oslo's few areas with this classic Norwegian village vibe. In 1988, the remaining wooden houses in the area were declared worthy of preservation.

På fritiden er jeg svært kreativ og elsker dans, fotografi, dikt og musikk. Og ja, jeg spiser desserten før middag.

name: Cute apartment by beautiful park
description:
This is a perfect apartment for late summer and fall with immediate proximity to Frogner Park! Although the apartment is very centrally located, the area is quiet.

The apartment has one large bedroom with a double bed facing a quiet garden plus a large bathroom w/ washing machine also facing the garden. The kitchen has everything you need to make a nice meal at home. You can also light the fireplace when autumn approaches.
neighborhood_overview:
The apartment is right by Frogner Park (Vigeland Park), where you will also find buses and trams, or you can walk about 10 minutes to Majorstukrysset to take the subway.

The shopping street Bogstadveien is also about a 7-minute walk from the apartment. It is also a short bus ride to beautiful Bygdøy island. SATS gym and the fantastic fancy food shops Jacobs and Smak av Italia ('Taste of Italy') are a five-minute walk away.

Vestkanttorget is a 2-minute walk from the apartment, here you will find one of Oslo's most popular markets on Saturdays. Here you will also find a local little cafe called "Happy Foods", serving vegetarian, dairy-free, and 90% vegan and gluten-free food.

name: Parkview Haven
description:
It's an urban location with 6 windows facing Sofienberg Park. To the left, trendy shops, cafes & restaurants. To the right, a short walk to the Botanical Gardens & Natural History Museum. Location is ideal for work, pleasure or both!

There is plenty of space for fun and relaxing with the whole family inside too, with tall ceilings and colorful walls - spending a day to recharge on maybe Grünerløkka's biggest couch, is a day not wasted!
host_about:
For my guests: 
I have been working in Oslo, Norway as a front desk receptionist since August 2015 and I love it! Ever since hearing about AirBnB, I have always wanted to host tourists of my own in my own place. Sharing my favorite place on earth with strangers and hearing how their stay was in a review or written in the cabin journal is something I find very fulfilling and I cannot wait to accommodate you!

Jeg er en serviceinnstilt person som ønsker å gjøre mitt beste for at mennesker som besøker både Sør og Nord-Norge, skal få mest mulig gode opplevelser. Akkurat dette ønsker jeg selv å oppleve på reiser i utlandet. 
Jeg setter stor pris på tilbakemeldinger og ønsker hele tiden å bli bedre på alt.

For hosts: 
I have recently graduated college in the U.S with a bachelor's degree in Psychology and minor in Anthropology- and it's time to get out and see more of Europe and beyond! So far I have visited Puerto Rico, Denmark, the Netherlands, Spain, Poland, France, Switzerland, the U.K, and Morocco. I am a rather care-free but safe traveler, open to new experiences and trusting new people. :)

neighborhood_overview:
Highly attractive and central location at Bislett. Situated on Eugenies gate, this super central location offers close proximity to everything the capital has to offer, including bustling restaurants and cafes, numerous shops and services, as well as excellent public transportation. Walking distance to two of the city's most sought-after shopping streets, Bogstadveien and Hegdehaugsveien, with a rich selection of stores and services. name: Et hjem for meg, et hjem for deg
description:
In this place you and your family can stay in one of the oldest areas in Oslo with the feel of old and new.
The apartment is a unique apartment similar to a four man's residence, very quiet and sheltered from the big city's impulses, but at the same time very central to Oslo's nicest and best parks, restaurants and sights
host_about:
Hei kjære deg/dere
Så hyggelig at dere ønsker å bli bedre kjent m meg. Jeg heter Sherry Hakimnejad og er opprinnelig fra Iran.  Har bodd i Norge i snart 40 år. Jeg elsker å reise og treffe folk derfor ønsker jeg å bruke Airbnb når jeg selv er på farta. 
Sist gang var i India,like før lock down. Det anbefales.

Jeg elsker Oslo og det er den byen jeg alltid kommer tilbake til. Kjenner byen godt så spør gjerne om ting å gjøre når du er her.
Jobben min har lenge vært livet mitt. Jeg er en sosial entreprenør og jobber med å skape arbeidsplasser for ungdommer som på ulike måter strever med å komme seg inni arbeidslivet og stå på egne ben. 
Jeg føler meg så heldig og privilegert som bor i Norge og ønsker å bruke det gullkortet til å bidra til et bedre verden. 

Jeg elsker natur, mat, familien min, mine kollegaer, trening og ikke minst jobben min. Jeg er veldig nysgjerrig og uredd som både kan gjøre at jeg noen ganger havner i merkelige situasjoner. Men som oftest har det gitt mer lærdom og erfaring. 

Livet er for kort til å la vær å leves og det starter ofte med et godt hvilested.

Velkommen til mitt hjem :-)

Apartment has 2 bedrooms with 2 single beds, but they can be put together into a double bed upon request. The kitchen is fully equipped to the smallest detail and has a dishwasher. The bathroom is spacious and has a washing machine. This beautiful building is from 1816 and has a historical value.
host_about: We are happy to offer you homelike places to stay during your travels. Established in 2000, Forenom offers guests ~9000 places to stay in Finland, Sweden, Norway, Denmark, and Germany. Our dedicated local teams in these countries work every day to ensure our guests have pleasant stays. We also offer on-demand housing throughout Europe to business travelers who will be staying for three months or more.

description:
A cosy apartment centrally located by alexander kiellands plass. You have a great balcony that is nice for breakfast, and a cozy living room to stay in if you want to take it easy. The apartment is located in a quiet area and you usually hear nothing of the local area, there is also a Sunday open shop just across the street.

The bus stopEvald Ryghs gate is only 3 minutes away, and takes you to the city center, there are also several bus lines with kiellands plass if you are going around Oslo.
